cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper is about meta-learning approaches for few-shot classification tasks, which are commonly studied in the fields of machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the performance of two base meta-learning models, which involves natural language processing, suggesting cs.CL (Computation and Language) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the use of bilevel optimization in the proposed framework may also relate to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
